### <span id="iv.iv.xxi-p0.1"></span>Chapter XXI.—The date of the martyrdom.

<span id="iv.iv.xxi-p1"></span>Now, the blessed Polycarp suffered
martyrdom on the second day of the month Xanthicus just begun, <span
id="fr_475"></span>[476](#fn_475.md) the seventh day before the Kalends of
May, on the great Sabbath, at the eighth hour. <span
id="fr_476"></span>[477](#fn_476.md) <span id="iv.iv.xxi-p3.5"></span>He
was taken by Herod, Philip the Trallian being high priest, <span
id="fr_477"></span>[478](#fn_477.md) Statius Quadratus being proconsul, but
Jesus Christ being King for ever, to whom be glory, honour, majesty, and
an everlasting throne, from generation to generation. Amen.

